cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DL

The paper discusses a system for computing fine-grained dependencies among the contents of the Mizar Mathematical Library, which is a formalized mathematical knowledge base. This involves analyzing the structure and relationships between mathematical definitions and proofs. This falls under the category of formal methods and automated reasoning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category, as the paper deals with formal logic and reasoning. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category, as the paper discusses a system for automated analysis of mathematical knowledge. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible sub-category, as the paper deals with the organization and structure of a large software artifact (the Mizar Mathematical Library). 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely sub-category, but still relevant as the Mizar system uses a specialized programming language for formalizing mathematics. 

cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is another possible sub-category, as the Mizar Mathematical Library is a digital resource for mathematical knowledge.
